{"segment_id": "00159", "page_num": 159, "segment": "To establish what we presented in Part I, we had to go beyond\ncase studies and stories and into rigorous research methods.\nThis allowed us to identify the practices that are the strongest\npredictors of success for all organizations of any size in any\nindustry.\n\nIn the first part of the book, we discussed the results of this\nresearch program and outlined why technology is a key value\ndriver and dierentiator for all organizations today. Now, we\npresent the science behind the research findings in Part I.", "source_file": "Forsgren N., Humble J., Kim G.- Accelerate. The Science of DevOps - 2018.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "16", "chapter_title": "Copyright (c) 2018 by Karen Whitley Bell and Steve Bell,", "section_num": "16.2", "section_title": "ING's New Agile Organizational Model Has No Fixed Structure--It", "l1_summary": "To establish what we presented in Part I, we had to go beyond\ncase studies and stories and into rigorous research methods. This allowed us to identify the practices that are the strongest\npredictors of success for all organizations of any size in any\nindustry. Now, we\npresent the science behind the...", "l2_summary": "To establish what we presented in Part I, we had to go beyond\ncase studies and stories and into rigorous research methods. This allowed us to identify the practices that are the strongest\npredictors of success for all organizations of any size in any\nindustry. In the first part of the book, we discussed the results of this\nresearch program and outlined why technology is a key value\ndriver and dierentiator for all organizations today. Now, we\npresent the science behind the research findings in Part I.", "prev_page": {"page_num": 158, "segment_id": "00158"}, "next_page": {"page_num": 160, "segment_id": "00160"}, "flags": {"continuity_gap": true}, "extended_fields": {"has_code": false, "has_formulas": fals