{"segment_id": "00204", "page_num": 204, "segment": "In Part III, they draw on their experiences at ING\nNetherlands, a global bank with over 34.4 million customers\nworldwide and with 52,000 employees, including more than\n9,000 engineers, to show the why and how of leadership,\nmanagement, and team practices that enable culture change.\nThis, in turn, enables sustainable high performance in a complex\nand dynamic environment.\n\nview beyond\n\nSteve and Karen extend our\n\nthe\ninterrelationships of team, management, and\nleadership\npractices, beyond the skillful adoption of DevOps, and beyond\nthe breaking down of silos--all necessary, but not sucient.\nHere we\nthe evolution of holistic, end-to-end\norganizational transformation, fully engaged and fully aligned to\nenterprise purpose.\n\nsee", "source_file": "Forsgren N., Humble J., Kim G.- Accelerate. The Science of DevOps - 2018.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "16", "chapter_title": "Copyright (c) 2018 by Karen Whitley Bell and Steve Bell,", "section_num": "16.2", "section_title": "ING's New Agile Organizational Model Has No Fixed Structure--It", "l1_summary": "In Part III, they draw on their experiences at ING\nNetherlands, a global bank with over 34.4 million customers\nworldwide and with 52,000 employees, including more than\n9,000 engineers, to show the why and how of leadership,\nmanagement, and team practices that enable culture change...", "l2_summary": "In Part III, they draw on their experiences at ING\nNetherlands, a global bank with over 34.4 million customers\nworldwide and with 52,000 employees, including more than\n9,000 engineers, to show the why and how of leadership,\nmanagement, and team practices that enable culture change. This, in turn, enables sustainable high performance in a complex\nand dynamic environment. Steve and Karen extend our the\ninterrelationships of team, management, and\nleadership\npractices, beyond the skillful